  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Intended use: pre-market submission support for a Class II CPB device; model outputs are used to bound hemolysis index across the device operating envelope (1–6 L/min, 2000–4000 RPM) as defined in the sponsor's predicate comparison strategy.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/hemolysis-worst-case-identification",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cfd-hemolysis-cpb-mrl2",
